<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
155. 
<taxonomicName LSID="38C17DD3-478F-56B7-A94E-38BF33B572AF" authority="Bornm., Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 43: 152. 1938. (Bornmueller 1938: 152)." authorityName="Bornm., Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 43: 152. 1938. (Bornmueller" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus suendermannii" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suendermannii">
Convolvulus suendermannii Bornm., Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 43: 152. 1938. (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bornmüller">Bornmueller</normalizedToken>
1938: 152).
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuzmanov" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Bornm." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri subsp. suendermannii" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="boissieri" subSpecies="suendermannii">Convolvulus boissieri subsp. suendermannii</taxonomicName>
(Bornm.) Kuzmanov, Fl. Nar. Republ. Bulgariya 8: 451 (1982). (
<bibRefCitation author="Kuzmanov, B" editor="Jordanov, D" journalOrPublisher="Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" pageId="205" pageNumber="206" pagination="443 - 463" refId="B182" refString="Kuzmanov, B, 1982. Convolvulaceae. In: Jordanov, D, Ed., Flora Reipublicae Popularis Bulgaricae volume 8. Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia: 443 - 463" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Reipublicae Popularis Bulgaricae volume 8." year="1982">Kuzmanov 1982</bibRefCitation>
: 451). Type. Based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bornm., Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 43: 152. 1938. (Bornmueller" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus suendermannii" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suendermannii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Convolvulus suendermannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bornm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
Plant from Bulgaria, Ali Botush Mountain, cultivated in Berlin, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sündermann">Suendermann</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
s.n. (holotype B!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
Intermediate between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steud., Nomencl. Bot., ed. 2, 1: 407. 1840. (Steudel" authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boissieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Convolvulus boissieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Syst. Nat. ed. 10, 2: 923. 1759. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lineatus" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Convolvulus lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Stems short, ascending; leaves sessile, obovate to oblanceolate, acute, cuneate to a broad base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Endemic to the area of Ali Botush Mountain, Bulgaria</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="166" lastPageNumber="167" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="166" pageNumber="167">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bornm., Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 43: 152. 1938. (Bornmueller" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus suendermannii" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suendermannii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">
<pageBreakToken pageId="166" pageNumber="167" start="start">Convolvulus</pageBreakToken>
suendermannii
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an interesting plant. We agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
(1967)
</bibRefCitation>
that it has the appearance of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Syst. Nat. ed. 10, 2: 923. 1759. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lineatus" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bornmüller’s">Bornmueller's</normalizedToken>
comment that it lies in &quot;apparent midposition&quot; between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Syst. Nat. ed. 10, 2: 923. 1759. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lineatus" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus compactus" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="compactus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus compactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily understandable because of its dwarf habit so it is not difficult to see why 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuzmanov, B" editor="Jordanov, D" journalOrPublisher="Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" pageId="205" pageNumber="206" pagination="443 - 463" refId="B182" refString="Kuzmanov, B, 1982. Convolvulaceae. In: Jordanov, D, Ed., Flora Reipublicae Popularis Bulgaricae volume 8. Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia: 443 - 463" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Reipublicae Popularis Bulgaricae volume 8." year="1982">Kuzmanov (1982)</bibRefCitation>
treated it as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. suendermannii" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="compactus" subSpecies="suendermannii">subsp. suendermannii</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steud., Nomencl. Bot., ed. 2, 1: 407. 1840. (Steudel" authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boissieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus boissieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It might well represent the hybrid 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Syst. Nat. ed. 10, 2: 923. 1759. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lineatus" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lineatus">Convolvulus lineatus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stace, Bot. J. Linn. Soc. 64: 58. 1971. (Stace" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri subsp. compactus" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="boissieri" subSpecies="compactus">Convolvulus boissieri subsp. compactus</taxonomicName>
. What adds to the interest is the type locality, which is precisely the same place where 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stoïanov">Stoianov</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
868 was collected. This is the plant whose identity troubled Turrill and 
<bibRefCitation author="Stace, CA" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="56 - 61" refId="B342" refString="Stace, CA, 1971. Notes on the European species of Convolvulus. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 64: 56 - 61" title="Notes on the European species of Convolvulus." volume="64" year="1971">Stace (1971</bibRefCitation>
: 57). If this is indeed a hybrid or intermediate in some way between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Syst. Nat. ed. 10, 2: 923. 1759. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lineatus" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lineatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus lineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stace, Bot. J. Linn. Soc. 64: 58. 1971. (Stace" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri subsp. compactus" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="boissieri" subSpecies="compactus">Convolvulus boissieri subsp. compactus</taxonomicName>
rather than a geographically anomalous population of 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. boissieri" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri subsp. boissieri" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="boissieri" subSpecies="boissieri">Convolvulus boissieri subsp. boissieri</taxonomicName>
, the geographical difficulties in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stace’s">Stace's</normalizedToken>
infraspecific classification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steud., Nomencl. Bot., ed. 2, 1: 407. 1840. (Steudel" authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boissieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus boissieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
disappear. Some support for this view is provided by the presence of a distinct peduncle-like stem in the part of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stoïanov">Stoianov</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
868 preserved in the envelope of the specimen at Kew. While the leaves are clearly those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steud., Nomencl. Bot., ed. 2, 1: 407. 1840. (Steudel" authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus boissieri" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boissieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus boissieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the inflorescence is thus atypical of that species and similar to that of the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bornm., Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 43: 152. 1938. (Bornmueller" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus suendermannii" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suendermannii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus suendermannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Another specimen (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Velčev">Velcev</normalizedToken>
et al.
</emphasis>
711 (W, E) from nearby Slavjanka appears to be the same taxon. Careful field observation is necessary to confirm whether or not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bornm., Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 43: 152. 1938. (Bornmueller" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus suendermannii" order="Solanales" pageId="166" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suendermannii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="166" pageNumber="167">Convolvulus suendermannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a hybrid. [
<bibRefCitation author="Strid, A" journalOrPublisher="Mountain Flora of Greece" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="13 - 20" refId="B352" refString="Strid, A, 1991. Convolvulus. Mountain Flora of Greece volume 2: 13 - 20" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 2" year="1991">Strid 1991</bibRefCitation>
: 18-20].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
